From 284ad966da5afe9c4b459c533ffebb7446d5d019 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chronium <chronium@interlink.local>
Date: Mon, 8 Jun 2026 17:27:41 +0700
Subject: [PATCH] chronium: per-profile performance.memory.jsHeapSizeLimit +
 navigator.connection (effectiveType,downlink,rtt,saveData) + storage.estimate
 quota + speechSynthesis.getVoices()
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds patch 0015 with 4 new fingerprint vectors, closing the gap vs ShardX
which a side-by-side TLS fingerprint comparison showed bypasses Cloudflare
Enterprise (grok.com) by surfacing this fuller set.

- FingerprintState gains MemoryFp / ConnectionFp / StorageFp /
  WebGLLimitsFp / VoiceList. SpeechVoices storage is a single TSV blob
  parsed on demand to avoid heap churn.
- 5 new switches (kFingerprintMemory, ...Connection, ...StorageQuota,
  ...WebGLLimits, ...SpeechVoices). FingerprintProfile parses 'memory',
  'connection', 'storage_estimate', 'webgl.max_*', 'speech.voices'
  from the profile JSON; chrome_content_browser_client appends to the
  renderer command line; chrome_content_renderer_client routes them
  into FingerprintState during RenderThreadStarted.
- Speech voices blob is hex-encoded over the CLI: voice names carry
  UTF-8 multibyte chars (français, 日本語) that AppendSwitchASCII
  mangles, and the TSV delimiters (\t \n) confuse CommandLineToArgvW.
- memory_info: override is applied in MemoryInfo's ctor AFTER the cache's
  QuantizeMemorySize step, so the profile value is the final js_heap_size_limit
  the JS sees. Pinning in GetHeapSize() alone is overwritten by the
  bucket-rounding path inside HeapSizeCache::Update.
- speech_synthesis: getVoices() returns the spoofed list directly and
  OnSetVoiceList is gated by a new fingerprint_voices_active_ flag so a
  late mojom reply can't race-overwrite the spoofed list.
